==English==
===Noun===
'''firm'''
#A [[business]] [[partnership]] of more than two persons.
#The [[name]] under which a [[company]] [[trade|trades]].

====Etymology====
From Spanish, Italian or Latin ''[[firma]]''

====Derived terms====
*[[firm up]]
*[[firmware]]

[[category:English nouns]]

===Adjective===
'''firm'''
#[[Resistant]] to [[apply|applied]] [[pressure]].
#[[Securely]] [[fix|fixed]] in [[place]].
#[[Constant]] or [[steadfast]].

====Etymology====
From Latin ''[[firmus]]''

====Derived terms====
*[[firmish]]
*[[firmly]]
*[[firmness]]

[[category:English adjectives]]

===Verb===
'''firm'''
#''(transitive)'' Make firm or strong; [[fix]] securely.
#''(transitive)'' Make compact or resistant to pressure; [[solidify]].
#''(intransitive)'' Become firm; [[stabilize]]; improve after decline.

====Etymology====
From Latin ''[[firmare]]''

